REASSURINGLY CONSERVATIVE
They came,
they saw, they went
away impressed.
This describes in brief form the
visit of the investigating fliers of the
Pan-American projects for an air line
between Manila and Hongkong, which
means an air connection for the Phil-
ippines with the wide world.
The go-
ing of the aviation investigators was
much like their coming.
It was with-
out storm and bluster.
It simply was
business like.
One of the most impressive demons-
trations in favor of the project which
they were here to investigate is found
in the manner of their coming and go-
ing.
They very
clearly
showed that
what they
are
investigating
can
be
done.
They did it.
They made the trip
both ways, made it with ease and such
safety that
they themselves
looked
upon it as a day's work.
Another impressive aspect to their
investigation was their conservative at-
titude.
They carefully refrained from
making sweeping statements indicative
of final decision in the matter.
They
gave indication of reasonable certainty
in their own minds,
but left the last
word until the final plans are approved.
That is far more reassuring than a lot
of promises about that on which they
could not yet be a hundred per cent
certain.
